race.comment: RAZANNE (12) peaks for a top barn off two placed efforts and he was heavily bet over 1400m at Pakenham last time (vet cleared). Will likely settle handy despite the awkward barrier and is well placed to be winning. PANELLI (7) spiked his figures placing at Yarra Valley over 1514m two starts back before leading and fading beaten 3L here over this trip. He was vet cleared and inclined to forgive. Has the blinkers on for the first time and rates to be right in it. MICKIDABEEL (2) ran well over a mile before the break and then didn't have the best of it from a wide gate at Yarra Valley first-up over 1500m. Will have to do it the hard way again but presents fitter and will hit the line. I AM TITAN (1) ran some tidy efforts earlier in the campaign but hasn't had much luck his last three. He won't be far away, putting his best foot forward. OLYMPIAD (6) is a likely improver from the McEvoy yard and John Allen rides today.
